Author: rehydrogenated
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] 🐧 Kinguin.io 🐧 - A Decentralized Marketplace for Gamers!🕹️
Body: Wow cool website! I really like the style. The name of the project is also pretty great.  One (or more) of these gaming tokens will really take off. I can see it gaining huge traction with gamers that are fairly loyal to a specific brand - like Blizzard fans.  The major issue I want to see addressed is: How do you plan to deal with cheaters, botters and farmers? How will they not tank the price of your token?

Author: Kinguin
Title: [ANN][PRE-ICO] 🐧 Kinguin.io 🐧 - A Decentralized Marketplace for Gamers!🕹️
Body: Glad to hear that you are enjoying our site and project.  In terms of our own GameClient for our Indie Game Developers, we will deal the same way with cheaters as everyone does - They will get banned from the game they attempted to cheat on. Besides that, we won't have much influence on cheaters getting banned on Steam/Origin or such.  That process won't affect the price/value of our token too much, as it depends more on the transactions happening through our marketplace, so everything from trades/coaching/gamekeys/...  Feel free to join our Telegram and we can answer you all the questions in there aswell.
